Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,...In the meantime, Lotte visited Frau Gerlach,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.92,0:00:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to make a plea with her, "Don't marry my dad," and such.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.52,0:00:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But that suggestion was ruled out.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.59,0:00:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, struck with the shock, \NLotte fell suddenly ill, feverish and delirious.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.37,0:00:22.34,Sign,,0,0,100,,{\c&HEAFCF9&\bord0\blur0.8\fs20}Episode 24 \N {\fs45} Hang on, Lotte!  \N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N {\fs23} \h Translation: Perevodildo | Timings: Sub-RoRo \h
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.28,0:00:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So you've been Luise this whole time...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.65,0:00:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm really sorry. We two must be \Nsome of the most unruly children ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.85,0:00:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We deceived mom and dad, \Nas if that was some game!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.23,0:00:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.96,0:00:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a very trying journey for you two, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.23,0:00:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Both me and your dad \Nowe you two a great debt of gratitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.33,0:01:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to you, your dad got to meet Lotte, \Nand the same for me - I finally met my Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.98,0:01:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you angry?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.13,0:01:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,How can I be angry?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.14,0:01:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You both grew up into such bright ladies. {lit is "you're already magnificent ladies" and idk how is that related to the next or previous line}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.27,0:01:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, there was but one time when you slipped up.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.67,0:01:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This photo?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.29,0:01:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It was supposed to be \Nat the bottom of the lake, in shreds.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.44,0:01:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,If the original negative is there, \Nthe photographer can make as many reprints as he needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.83,0:01:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But Lotte, what's up with you now?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.37,0:01:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Before, I used to collect your letters \Nfrom the post office daily. But lately - nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.38,0:01:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Letters?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.67,0:01:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been to there today, yesterday, \Nthe day before yesterday, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.09,0:01:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But each time, there's no General Delivery for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.77,0:01:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure... I'm sure, something happened to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.29,0:01:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,There's this uneasiness in my chest, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.31,0:02:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, mom, can we call Vienna?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.91,0:02:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we talk to dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.82,0:02:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. Now that I had found out, \NI guess we ought to let your father know, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.49,0:02:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm also concerned about Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.83,0:02:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Körner, as a father for Lotte, I believe...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.27,0:02:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,No... I mean, I want to eat breakfast... {no clue what he means to say, but this can only be the breakfast}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.10,0:02:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Not good enough either... {I hope this pin to is "first; top; best; number one​"}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.11,0:02:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, whichever I choose, \NI just need to propose boldly and openly. {may be "magnificent; grand; impressive; dignified; majestic; imposing; stately" but may be "grandly; boldly; confidently"}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.02,0:02:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.46,0:02:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, please do me this favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.53,0:03:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait. I guess I should call him, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.47,0:03:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Who could that be at such hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.95,0:03:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Editor-in-Chief Bernau?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.05,0:03:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Lotte, good evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.01,0:03:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I promised to your mom earlier, \Nthat I'd come visit you two tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.45,0:03:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so? You promised her?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.39,0:03:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean... Sure. \NCome in, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.71,0:03:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Master, you got a phone call.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.18,0:03:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Phone call?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.52,0:03:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell them I can't. {/refuse}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.49,0:04:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I did just that. But they say it's urgent \Nand demand that you answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.69,0:04:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's someone called Körner, if I got it right...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.06,0:04:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Körner?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.48,0:04:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it Körner? The one who called?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.93,0:04:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that's just what she said...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.71,0:04:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello? Palfy listening.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.52,0:04:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.95,0:04:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.86,0:04:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry I'm calling so suddenly...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.44,0:04:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing is, I'm worried about my child.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.60,0:04:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Could she possibly be sick or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.44,0:04:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's exactly the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.34,0:04:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But... How did you possibly...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.34,0:04:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,My... She really is?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.61,0:04:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, please hear me out calmly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.98,0:05:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The actual Luise is here with me, \Nshe confided to me everything that happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.68,0:05:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute there! What do you mean? \NMy Luise is now...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.45,0:05:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the one in your house is Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.81,0:05:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The two have switched places.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.60,0:05:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Switched places?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.22,0:05:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. When it was the time for them \Nto return home from the summer camp,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.63,0:05:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise pretended to be Lotte and returned to me, \Nand Lotte took Luise's place by your side.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.78,0:05:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, just like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.01,0:05:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But these days, Lotte went out of touch with her. {lit: it seems, this place stopped receiving contact from lotte}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.15,0:05:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, she was wondering, \N"Is Lotte ill or something?"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.28,0:05:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on? \NAt this rate, I'm falling ill myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.35,0:05:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Please be lenient to these children! {don't scold; to chide; to rebuke; to reprimand}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.72,0:05:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Considering what these girls had been through, \Nyou can't judge them. {if you think about their feelings, you can't to condemn; to blame; to criticize; to criticise; to reproach; to accuse}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.69,0:05:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,How is Lotte looking? {/condition}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.59,0:05:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, that...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.29,0:05:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In bed, struck by a terrible fever.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.89,0:05:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And well...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.60,0:05:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The cause seems to be psychological. {/mental}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.57,0:05:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.51,0:06:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But say... Is there anything I can do to help?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.02,0:06:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Most certainly, you can! That...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.86,0:06:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.47,0:06:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheesh... What's with those two at a moment like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.80,0:06:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad! Dad, you hear me? This me - Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.07,0:06:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you imagine, \Nhow much we two are worried about Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.51,0:06:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Would it help, \Nif us two come to Vienna now?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.28,0:06:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.35,0:06:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That sounds like a jolly good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.22,0:06:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You {\i1}should{\i0} come. The sooner the better. {/it would help, but make it quick}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.35,0:06:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.79,0:06:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.26,0:06:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. If you come here now, she might just... {he uses you in singular here}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.10,0:06:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte will definitely get better.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.10,0:06:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In her delirium, she is constantly calling out to you. {/crying in sleep}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.46,0:06:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,"Mom,"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.90,0:07:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.83,0:07:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,If possible, please come at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.73,0:07:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, I understand. \NI'll make every effort to get there sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.50,0:07:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.65,0:07:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Great! Mom, let's rush to the airport!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.55,0:07:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.19,0:07:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We won't find any plane at this hour! \NAn the last train to Vienna is gone already!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.83,0:07:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Editor? Have you been here for long?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.48,0:07:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Quite some while already. \NI overheard everything that happened here. {lit: everything since long ago, I heard}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.50,0:07:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't mean to, of course... {most likely he means "it was rude/I gotta apologize" tho I can't rule out some "it seems dire for you" or w/e}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.74,0:07:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, no, it's fine...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.21,0:07:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry! Your promise from earlier \Nhad slipped my mind completely! {about tonight}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.55,0:07:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Come one, hurry up. \NWe're going on an overnight drive to Vienna. {dead of night; midnight}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.77,0:08:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.94,0:08:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Turns out, you are my another daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.44,0:08:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That timid little Lotte...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.78,0:08:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.27,0:08:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you managed such a switch... {not sure what he means, maybe that lotte is/was small and she got enough guts to switch places}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.58,0:08:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Resi! Resi!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.60,0:08:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes, anything I can do for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.58,0:08:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Something with Fraulein?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.08,0:08:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No, tomorrow, my wife comes here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.86,0:08:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Counting on you to prepare the meal and such.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.25,0:08:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? You mean, your bride? {actually it's another word for wife}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.56,0:08:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The wife that I broke up with!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.60,0:08:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise is coming with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.27,0:08:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Fraulein Luise had finally gotten better? {lit: sick and in the room}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.47,0:08:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah? No... Well anyway, just take care of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.61,0:08:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me that the fatigue from looking after her \Nhad driven Master delirious as well? {tired from nursing (a patient)}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.85,0:08:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What do I do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.73,0:09:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, he said the reason is psychological...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.70,0:09:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What in the world could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.17,0:09:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There's one thing I know of \Nthat may or may not have something to do with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.09,0:09:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.90,0:09:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That... I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.10,0:09:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, for the last few months, \Ndad has been seeing a woman named Irene Gerlach. {/dating}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.96,0:09:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a suspicion, \Nthis might just be the case. {/have something to do}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.20,0:09:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.28,0:11:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Right there, Editor Bernau!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.52,0:11:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Editor-in-Chief, I really don't know \Nif I'll ever be able to repay this...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.13,0:11:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you worry about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.36,0:11:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather, hurry up to check on Lotte, Miss Körner.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.51,0:11:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, hurry, hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.08,0:11:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise! Going outside with a fever like that... \NI swear, she is intractable. {hard to deal with; hard to handle; difficult; trying; intractable; incorrigible; refractory}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.52,0:11:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Peperl! Long time no see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.26,0:12:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Fraulein Luise, is it all right for you to get out of bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.19,0:12:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be any other way than all right for me. {/It's been ... for me all along}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.59,0:12:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The one with the fever is Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.97,0:12:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you, I'm Körner
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.60,0:12:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,My! You're the wife Master told me about... {anata sama ... no?}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.64,0:12:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Resi, to meet you, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.54,0:12:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, how is it looking for Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.78,0:12:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If you mean the girl struck by a fever, \Nthat had been Fraulein Luise. And as you can see...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.88,0:12:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Told you you're wrong! \NThe one with the fever is Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.59,0:12:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,After me, mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.33,0:12:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Not so fast, Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.17,0:12:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor Strobl! It's been a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.80,0:12:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't give me that "a while!" \NIt's way too soon for you to get up! {dame/dare janai ka?}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.10,0:12:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm not even the one who fell ill!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.38,0:12:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop! You can't just disregard the doctor! {no clue what's okanakatte can be here, but lit is "you can't not do iku to the doctor" so would asuume listening}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.35,0:12:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, stop at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.56,0:12:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.95,0:12:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.30,0:13:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.80,0:13:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.53,0:13:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.77,0:13:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay. You don't have to say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.41,0:13:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,How does it feel to be back, Luise? {no clue what he means, maybe "I'm glad you're back" or "it's good you returned"}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.34,0:13:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.52,0:13:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.89,0:13:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I see two Luises!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.86,0:13:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,There were actually two girls, \Ntwo twin sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.89,0:13:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But in unexpected turn of events, \Nthey switched places.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.77,0:13:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Switched places, then? \NStill, such a thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.85,0:14:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, mom is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.98,0:14:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.55,0:14:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.36,0:14:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.47,0:14:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, mom is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.42,0:14:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.09,0:14:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.89,0:14:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, your mom is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.03,0:14:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I am here with you, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.43,0:14:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, it's me, Luise. You recognize me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.97,0:14:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.34,0:14:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But... why?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.28,0:14:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine now, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.92,0:14:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't have to worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.70,0:15:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, get better soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.21,0:15:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.54,0:15:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, don't worry now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.32,0:15:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently, even a check-up wouldn't be necessary. {/i won't even have to look at it}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.36,0:15:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,From now on, she'll recover by herself, \Nprovided the appetite is there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.47,0:16:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, here you go, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.40,0:16:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.17,0:16:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the one that is Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.93,0:16:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, Fraulein Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.71,0:16:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, the one sleeping \Non the second floor would be...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.29,0:16:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.28,0:16:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your hard work!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.07,0:16:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, Lotte. Say "Aah."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.93,0:16:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Delicious...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.43,0:16:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.53,0:16:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, you should eat it all \Nand recover in the shortest time!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.00,0:16:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.34,0:16:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It appears, we can trust Luise \Nto take care of Lotte now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.52,0:16:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't we go downstairs now \Nto catch a breath, at last?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.13,0:17:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Editor-in-Chief...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.40,0:17:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been some years...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.81,0:17:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Seven of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.66,0:17:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Seven years, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.00,0:17:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It sounds like a long time, \Nyet they also passed in a blink of an eye, somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.17,0:17:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a good point.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.33,0:17:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, and that man...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.28,0:17:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this chap, Editor-in-Chief Bernau...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.45,0:17:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Is he...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.28,0:17:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I mean... Did he make a proposal already?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.25,0:17:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,To you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.10,0:18:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,A proposal? To me? Why should he?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.50,0:18:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no need to disavow anything now. {/hide}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.30,0:18:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, back then... \NIn Munich, albeit I didn't know who he is yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.24,0:18:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I met him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.04,0:18:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,When I saw him at Don Giovanni's,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.79,0:18:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,it was apparent,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.61,0:18:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,he was there to propose to a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.92,0:18:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And the one he was supposed to meet there \Nwas none other than you. {/you were the one who appeared}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.24,0:18:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Editor-in-Chief...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.27,0:18:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.92,0:19:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Ubiquitous to grown-ups, but unknown to children, \Nthe complicated ways of heart are often hard to grasp. {lit: there are complex movements of the heart - no clue what he means originally}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.32,0:19:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte and Luise, just happy at being reunited again, {added}\Nrelish this moment of tranquility.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.57,0:19:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly, both are going to see \Nthe most delightful dreams tonight. {rather, he says it in present continuous, so it's prolly lotte who is seeing them now}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.74,0:20:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Forever and ever, let us offer a prayer \Nthat the happiness of the two is never disturbed.
Comment: 0,0:20:08.87,0:20:08.87,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.81,0:20:18.34,Sign,,0,0,0,,A miserable romance {可哀想ね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.34,0:20:21.80,Sign,,0,0,0,,A tear-jerking nuance {涙誘うニュアンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.80,0:20:25.52,Sign,,0,0,0,,If you turn another page of your memories, {想い出のページめくれば}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.52,0:20:28.43,Sign,,0,0,0,,Here she is - heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン} {actually, "the heroine of the recollections" but that doesn't have a nice ring to it}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.65,0:20:40.07,Sign,,0,0,0,,I raise my eyes to your face - {あなたの面影　見上げて咲いている}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.07,0:20:43.83,Sign,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, I'm in full bloom {unsure, maybe "it's flourishing"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.83,0:20:47.37,Sign,,0,0,0,,A sunflower amidst the blizzard - {act. in the middle of winter}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.37,0:20:50.77,Sign,,0,0,0,,that would be me, my dear {真冬のひまわり　それが私なの}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.21,0:20:53.94,Sign,,0,0,0,,Always on the verge of freezing, {凍えるような気持ちでいつも}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.79,0:20:57.34,Sign,,0,0,0,,My feelings are out of control -
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.34,0:21:01.89,Sign,,0,0,0,,Too stiff to even say "Do you still love me?" {「好き?」と尋くこともできず}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.89,0:21:06.04,Sign,,0,0,0,,My lips just keep wavering in this wind! {風に揺れていたわ}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.59,0:21:11.24,Sign,,0,0,0,,A pitiful Romance {いじらしいね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.24,0:21:14.65,Sign,,0,0,0,,Something that only happens in dreams - {夢のような出来事}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.65,0:21:18.28,Sign,,0,0,0,,Trying hard to forget, I fell even more in love {忘れるために愛したの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.28,0:21:21.05,Sign,,0,0,0,,with heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.10,0:21:25.87,Sign,,0,0,0,,Miracle that I came across now is hugging me tight {めぐりあえた奇跡　そっと抱きしめて}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.87,0:21:29.28,Sign,,0,0,0,,This is the story of my life, my duty is to protect it! {私だけの歴史　守ってゆくわ}
Comment: 0,0:21:32.87,0:21:32.87,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.27,0:21:34.79,Sign,,0,0,0,,Next episode preview
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.60,0:21:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, I finally return to being Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.13,0:21:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, who is boyish!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.04,0:21:43.21,Sign,,0,0,0,,I also return to being Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.31,0:21:47.07,Sign,,0,0,0,,Great!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.07,0:21:48.11,Sign,,0,0,0,,Great indeed!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.11,0:21:49.64,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Dad and mom...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.64,0:21:50.48,Sign,,0,0,0,,Maybe they can...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.48,0:21:51.85,Sign,,0,0,0,,They definitely can...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.85,0:21:53.01,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Reconcile!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.01,0:21:56.45,Sign,,0,0,0,,How can they not, when they have \Nsuch amicable mood between them? {atmosphere; mood; ambience; ambiance; aura; feel}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.85,0:21:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time in I and Myself:
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.69,0:22:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Love Reborn!? {よみがえった愛!?}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.72,0:22:03.82,Sign,,0,0,0,,Episode 25 \NLove Reborn!? {よみがえった愛!?} {/revived}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.29,0:22:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Look forward to it!{\i0}
